Michael J. Merriman Jr., CPA: Executive Profile & Biography - Bloomberg









































  





















































































July 21, 2017 9:21 PM ET
Capital Markets

Company Overview of Glengary LLC



SnapshotPeople 




OverviewBoard MembersCommittees



Executive Profile
Michael J. Merriman Jr., CPAFounding Partner, Glengary LLCAgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 11 Board Members in 11 different organizations across 13 different industries.See Board Relationships61--
Background

		Mr. Michael J. Merriman, Jr., also known as Mike, CPA, has been an Operating Advisor at Resilience Capital Partners LLC since July 1, 2008. Mr. Merriman joined Resilience Capital Partners in July 1, 2008 in the operations team. Previously, he was an Operating Partner at the Resilience Capital Partners LLC. He is a Founding Partner at Glengary LLC. He is a Founder of The Entrepreneurs EDGE, Inc. He served as the Chief Executive Officer and President at The Lamson & Sessions ... Co. from November 15, 2006 to 2007. He served as the Senior Vice President and Chief Financial Officer at American Greetings Corp. from September 1, 2005 to November 2006 where he led the M&A activities and facilitated the refinancing and repurchasing of a third of the company's outstanding shares. He served as a Director of Marketing Specialists Corporation since August 18, 1999. From August 1995 to March 31, 2004, he served as Chief Executive Officer and President of Royal Appliance Mfg. Co. Inc. and served as its Chief Financial Officer from 1992 to 1995. He joined Royal in 1992 as a Vice President of Finance. From 1978 to 1992, he worked with Arthur Andersen & Co., and became a Partner in Special Services Division in 1990. He was Partner of Arthur Andersen LLP. He has been the Chairman of CR Brands, Inc., since October 2012 and serves as its Director. He has been a Director of Invacare Corporation since May 15, 2014 and American Greetings Corp. since 2014. He has been a Director of Century Intermediate Holding Company since January 24, 2014. He has been an Independent Director of Tomy International, Inc., since 2004. Mr. Merriman serves as a Member of Business Advisory Board at Ganeden, Inc. He has been an Independent Director of Nordson Corporation since August 19, 2008. He has been an Independent Director of Regis Corp. since August 2011. He has been an Independent Director of Omnova Solutions Inc. since March 2008 and serves as its Presiding Director. He serves as a Director of John Carroll University, True Hero, Inc., The Singing Angels, Boys Hope Girls Hope New York Inc., Boys Hope Girls Hope of Northeast Ohio and Students in Free Enterprise (SIFE), where he was a national Chairman. Mr. Merriman served as an Independent Director of RC2 Corp. from 2004 to April 2011. He served as Director of Hospice Of The Western Reserve, Inc. and Glengary LLC. He served as Director of American Greetings Corp. from November 2006 to October 2013. He served as Director of Royal Appliance Mfg. Co. Inc. from October 1993 to March 31, 2004 and The Lamson & Sessions Co. Mr. Merriman is a Certified Public Accountant. He holds a B.S. in Business Administration from John Carroll University.Read Full Background




